title: Obama celebrates American music with 'eclectic bunch'
text:
Susan Walsh Obama celebrates American music with 'eclectic bunch' 
President Barack Obama walks onto the stage in the East Room of the White House in Washington at the beginning of the "In Performance at the White House" series, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015. This event, “A Celebration of American Creativity" will celebrate the 50th anniversary of the National Foundation on the Arts and the Humanities Act. (AP Photo/Susan Walsh) Susan Walsh Obama celebrates American music with 'eclectic bunch' 
Three-time American Grammy Award-winning blues musician Keb' Mo' performs in the East Room of the White House in Washington at the beginning of the “In Performance at the White House” series, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015. This event, “A Celebration of American Creativity,” will celebrate the 50th anniversary of the National Foundation on the Arts and the Humanities Act. (AP Photo/Susan Walsh) Susan Walsh Obama celebrates American music with 'eclectic bunch'

Three-time American Grammy Award-winning blues musician Keb' Mo' performs in the East Room of the White House in Washington at the beginning of the “In Performance at the White House” series, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015. This event, “A Celebration of American Creativity,” will celebrate the 50th anniversary of the National Foundation on the Arts and the Humanities Act. (AP Photo/Susan Walsh) Posted: Wednesday, October 14, 2015 9:12 pm 
WASHINGTON (AP) — Swaying to jazz and blues tunes while bopping his head to the beat, President Barack Obama is celebrating what he calls one of the country's most precious gifts: "American creativity."
